Given vectors $\vec{m}=( \sqrt{3}\sin x,\sin x )$, $\vec{n}=( \cos x,\sin x )$.

$(1)$ If $\vec{m}\parallel\vec{n}$ and $x\in \left[ 0,\frac{\pi }{2} \right]$, find the angle $x$;

$(2)$ If $f(x)=\vec{m}\cdot\vec{n}$, find the smallest positive period and the interval of monotonic increase for the function $f(x)$.

Given the polar equation of curve $C_1$ as $\rho^2\cos2\theta=8$, and the polar equation of curve $C_2$ as $\theta= \frac {\pi}{6}$, curves $C_1$ and $C_2$ intersect at points A and B.  
(Ⅰ) Find the polar coordinates of points A and B;  
(Ⅱ) Curve $C_1$ intersects with the line $\begin{cases} x=2+ \frac { \sqrt {3}}{2}t \\ y= \frac {1}{2}t \end{cases}$ (where $t$ is a parameter) at points M and N, respectively. Find the length of segment MN.

Find all real-coefficient polynomials \( f(x) \) that satisfy the following conditions: 
(1) \( f(x) = a_{0} x^{2n} + a_{2} x^{2n-2} + \cdots + a_{2n-2} x^{2} + a_{2n} \), where \( a_{0} > 0 \);
(2) \( \sum_{j=0}^{n} a_{2j} a_{2n-2j} \leq \binom{2n}{n} \cdot a_{0} a_{2n} \);
(3) The polynomial \( f(x) \) has \( 2n \) pure imaginary roots.
(Problem from the 1997 China National Mathematical Olympiad Team Selection Contest)

Given the function $f(x)=\lg \frac {1-x}{1+x}$,
(1) Find the domain of the function and determine its monotonicity;
(2) Solve the inequality $f(2x-1) < 0$ with respect to $x$.

A portion of the graph of \( g(x) = dx^2 + ex + f \) is shown below. The distance between grid lines on the graph is \( 1 \) unit.

What is the value of \( d+e+3f \)?

[asy]
size(150);
real ticklen=3;
real tickspace=2;

real ticklength=0.1cm;
real axisarrowsize=0.14cm;
pen axispen=black+1.3bp;
real vectorarrowsize=0.2cm;
real tickdown=-0.5;
real tickdownlength=-0.15inch;
